With the amendment of the Constitution, the regime does not change in Turkey, the executive does not end, the Assembly does not close, the judiciary is not neutralized.
It redefines the relationship between executive, legislative and judicial bodies, and ensures that everyone is engaged in their real work.
We have the authority to elect the President who will direct the country, remove all intermediaries, and directly provide the national government.
We ensure that the Turkish Grand National Assembly is the essential element of the legislature and strengthen the authority of the President and the government.
We aim to strengthen the independence of the judiciary with its impartiality and to prevent judicial debate in the past.
We will strengthen democracy by weakening democracy with the Constitutional amendment, which will be presented to the discretion of our nation on April 16th.
